  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA76-kiḷavi">itu puṇarntuṭaṉpōkāniṉṟa talaiva ṉiṭaiccurattut talaivik kuraittatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is what HE said to HER in the middle of the desert when they were eloping after union.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA76">
<l>          varumaḻai karanta vāṉiṟa vicumpi</l>
<l>          ṉuṇṭuḷi māṟiya vulavai yaṅkāṭ</l>
<l>          ṭāla nīḻa lacaivu nīkki</l>
<l>          yañcuvaḻi yañcā tacaivaḻi yacaii</l>
<l>          varuntā tēkumati vāliḻaik kuṟumaka </l>
<l>          ḷimmeṉ pēralar nummūrp puṉṉai</l>
<l>          vīmala rutirnta tēṉāṟu pulaviṟ</l>
<l>          kāṉa lārmaṇaṉ marīik</l>
<l>          kalluṟac civantaniṉ mellaṭi yuyaṟkē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Repelling the weariness in the Banyan shade</l>
<l rend="indent3">in the pretty wilderness</l>
<l rend="indent2">with green twigs that have become changed with the fine drops</l>
<l rend="indent2">from the pure-coloured sky that is hidden by the coming rain,</l>
<l rend="indent">resting on the moving way without fear for the fearful way,</l>
<l>go without suffering, little woman with pure jewels,</l>
<l rend="indent2">so that your soft feet reddened by the stone may escape,</l>
<l rend="indent2">joining together in the full sand of the seashore grove</l>
<l rend="indent3">with [its] smell of fish, fragrant with the honey dropped</l>
<l rend="indent3">from the many blossoms(?)<note place="foot">Do we have to read <term xml:lang="ta">vī-malar</term> as two quasi-synonyms for "blossom" as referring to great number, or is it rather <term xml:lang="ta">vī malar</term> "perishing blossoms"?</note> of the Puṉṉai trees</l>
<l rend="indent3">by your village of resounding great gossip.</l>
      </lg>
         </div>
          </body>
